    "body": "### Description\n\nAccording to the Postgres Language Server's [Configuration docs](https://pgtools.dev/#configuration) (emphasis mine):\n\n> We recommend that you create a `postgrestools.jsonc` configuration file for each project. This eliminates the need to repeat the CLI options each time you run a command, and ensures that we use the same configuration in your editor. Some options are also only available from a configuration file. **If you are happy with the defaults, you donâ€™t need to create a configuration file.** To create the `postgrestools.jsonc` file, run the `init` command in the root folder of your project:\n\nSingle file support for `postgres_lsp` was disabled in #3657. However, the referenced documentation makes me think we should not require a `postgrestools.jsonc` file.",
